President Muhammadu Buhari on Tuesday sent a letter to the Senate,  seeking its approval for the payment of N10bn to Kogi State. Buhari, in the letter, addressed to Senate President,  Ahmad Lawan,  said the money would be used by the state government to settle local debts it incurred as a result of the projects executed on behalf of the Federal Government. READ ALSO  PDP says attack on Oshiomhole signals disintegration in APC Buhari said his request was based on the resolution passed by the eighth Senate.